HEADWORD: Appendicularia
<hw>Ap`pen*dic`u*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small free-swimming
Tunicata, shaped somewhat like a tadpole, and remarkable for
resemblances to the larv⟦ae⟧ of other Tunicata. It is the type of the
order Copelata or Larvalia. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

